      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush vs. Gore, Round 1: Now the People Debate; Expertise Preferred</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rosary Uzzolino Lescohier letter disputes October 4 article on debate between Gov George W Bush and Vice Pres Al Gore</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''In the Spotlight, the Debaters Stick to What They Do Best'' (front page, Oct. 4):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''In the Spotlight, the Debaters Stick to What They Do Best'' (front page, Oct. 4):</p>
        <p>What is the problem with Al Gore's ''digressing to explain things'' or with his being knowledgeable about foreign affairs? I fail to see this as a disqualifier for the job of the leader of our country.</p>
        <p>I expect our leaders to instruct by precept, example or experience and to be knowledgeable.</p>
        <p>ROSARY UZZOLINO LESCOHIER  Morristown, N.J., Oct. 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
